							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ravgrewalkok/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Rav-Grewal-Kok-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Rav-Grewal-Kok.jpeg 2x" alt="Rav Grewal-Kök" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ravgrewalkok/">Rav Grewal-Kök</a></h6>
										Rav Grewal-Kök’s stories have appeared in <em>The Atlantic</em>, <em>Ploughshares</em>, <em>New England Review</em>, <em>Missouri Review</em>, <em>Gulf Coast</em>, and elsewhere. He has won an NEA fellowship in prose and is a fiction editor at <em>Fence</em>. He grew up in Hong Kong and on Vancouver Island and now lives in Los Angeles. <em>The Snares</em> is his first novel.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
